    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-03-26T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-03-26T18:00:00-05:00" n="440"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d440">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">701.9111/535: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Merriam</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-03-26T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 26, 1936—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>12. Department’s 10 [<hi rend="italic">11</hi>], March 19, 4 p.m. <hi
                        rend="italic">Daily Mirror</hi> today printed following under heading
                    “Correction”: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“It has been brought to the attention of the <hi rend="italic"
                                >Mirror</hi> that a statement contained in its issue of February 8,
                            1936, to the effect that His Majesty, the Shah of Iran, was formerly in
                            the hire of the British Legation at Teheran, is wholly without
                            foundation, and that His Majesty has since his earliest youth served his
                            country in the army.</p>
                        <p>“The <hi rend="italic">Mirror</hi> regrets the publication in its columns
                            of such an erroneous statement and is happy to make this
                            correction.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
